---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import Button from "../../components/ui/Button.astro";
import MigrationMap from "../../components/ui/MigrationMap.astro";
import ShortcutFoxWarning from "../../components/ui/ShortcutFoxWarning.astro";
import GlossaryTerm from "../../components/glossary/GlossaryTerm.astro";
---
<BaseLayout
  title="SEO & Hosting Provider Transfer | Boho Digital"
  description="Switch providers without losing the trail. Boho Digital helps map transfers, preserve search value, and document the handoff."
  image="/assets/backgrounds/forest-mist.webp"
>
  <section class="page-hero section-forest image-backed">
    <div class="container page-hero-grid">
      <div class="hero-panel" data-reveal>
        <div class="breadcrumbs">
          <a href="/">Home</a>
          <span>/</span>
          <a href="/services/">Services</a>
          <span>/</span>
          <strong>SEO &amp; Hosting Provider Transfer</strong>
        </div>
        <p class="eyebrow">SEO &amp; Hosting Provider Transfer</p>
        <h1>Switch providers without losing the trail.</h1>
        <p class="hero-lead">
          Moving away from an old SEO agency, hosting provider, website platform, or
          messy vendor setup can be stressful. Boho Digital helps map the transfer,
          preserve search value, and clean up the handoff step by step.
        </p>
        <div class="page-actions">
          <Button href="/contact/">Ask about a transfer</Button>
          <Button href="/ask-the-owl/dictionary/" variant="secondary">Open the Dictionary</Button>
        </div>
      </div>
      <aside class="hero-side-panel" data-reveal="left">
        <p class="micro-label">What we help transfer</p>
        <ul class="ledger-list">
          <li>SEO agency setups and reporting layers</li>
          <li>Hosting accounts and platform migrations</li>
          <li>DNS and registrar changes</li>
          <li>Analytics and Search Console continuity</li>
          <li>Redirect plans and owner-facing documentation</li>
        </ul>
      </aside>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container chapter-grid">
      <article class="section-card" data-reveal>
        <p class="eyebrow">Why transfers get messy</p>
        <p>
          Credentials go missing. Old providers hold the map too tightly. Tracking was
          never documented. A move that looks simple on the surface is often hiding
          fragile dependencies in <GlossaryTerm slug="dns" />, hosting, analytics, or
          page structure.
        </p>
      </article>
      <article class="section-card" data-reveal="left">
        <p class="eyebrow">What we help transfer</p>
        <p>
          Domain and registrar access, hosting environments, CMS platforms, analytics
          layers, Search Console visibility, <GlossaryTerm slug="redirect-map" />,
          metadata, and the parts of the site people forget until launch day.
        </p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section-band-mist">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-heading compact" data-reveal>
        <p class="eyebrow">Migration map</p>
        <h2>Controlled movement beats brave chaos.</h2>
      </div>
      <MigrationMap steps={["Inventory", "Preserve", "Plan", "Move", "Verify", "Document"]} />
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container chapter-grid">
      <article class="section-card" data-reveal>
        <p class="eyebrow">SEO preservation checklist</p>
        <ul class="ledger-list">
          <li>Current high-value URLs and search pages identified</li>
          <li><GlossaryTerm slug="metadata" /> and title logic reviewed</li>
          <li><GlossaryTerm slug="redirect-map" /> drafted before launch</li>
          <li><GlossaryTerm slug="google-search-console" /> access confirmed</li>
          <li>Post-launch crawl and indexing checks scheduled</li>
        </ul>
      </article>
      <article class="section-card" data-reveal="left">
        <p class="eyebrow">Hosting transfer checklist</p>
        <ul class="ledger-list">
          <li><GlossaryTerm slug="hosting-provider" /> and platform access inventory</li>
          <li><GlossaryTerm slug="dns" /> records documented before changes</li>
          <li>Forms, email, and integrations noted</li>
          <li>Analytics continuity plan prepared</li>
          <li>Owner-facing documentation created after the move</li>
        </ul>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section-band-terracotta">
    <div class="container chapter-grid">
      <ShortcutFoxWarning
        title="Provider red flags worth catching early."
        body="Watch for reluctance to share access, unclear account ownership, suspiciously vague migration promises, and anything that smells like provider lock-in."
      />
      <div class="section-card" data-reveal="left">
        <p class="eyebrow">FAQs</p>
        <div class="faq-stack">
          <div>
            <h3>What if we only have part of the login trail?</h3>
            <p>That is common. The first stage is often figuring out what exists, what is missing, and what matters first.</p>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h3>Can you work alongside our developer or host?</h3>
            <p>Yes. Boho often acts as the mapkeeper for search, tracking, and handoff quality while other technical work moves in parallel.</p>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h3>Does this stop at launch?</h3>
            <p>No. The transfer includes verification and documentation so ownership is clearer after the move than before it.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="service-highlight final-cta-panel" data-reveal>
        <p class="eyebrow">Final CTA</p>
        <h2>Bring the messy stack. We will help map the handoff.</h2>
        <p>
          You do not need perfect documentation before reaching out. Send what you know
          and Boho will help identify the missing pieces.
        </p>
        <div class="cta-actions">
          <Button href="/contact/">Start the transfer conversation</Button>
          <Button href="/ask-the-owl/dictionary/provider-lock-in/" variant="secondary">Read about provider lock-in</Button>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
